DESCRIPTION: With the full system reassembled, place the black multimeter lead directly on the physical negative terminal of the 12 V battery and the red lead on: (a) the PSU negative output cable terminal, (b) the negative terminals of each control module pair in sequence, and (c) the negative input cable terminal at the load module. In each case, measure resistance/continuity with power off and voltage with power on. Confirm that the battery negative is actually common to the entire 0 V return path and that there is not an unintended series element or open between battery negative and the rest of the circuit.,
