Instruction: With the system powered, place the black multimeter lead on the physical negative terminal of the battery. Using the red lead, first measure DC voltage at the battery positive terminal, then at the internal node feeding the green supply LED/resistor, then at the solder/terminal point where the external + output cable connects inside the PSU box. Verify that battery + actually appears at the PSU + output. With power off, measure resistance from battery + to the PSU + output cable to check for an unexpected series element or open circuit.
