- ctrl7_green_led: Power Flow Indicator (green) 7
- ctrl7_green_resistor: Power Flow Indicator Resistor 7
- ctrl8_green_led: Power Flow Indicator (green) 8
- ctrl8_green_resistor: Power Flow Indicator Resistor 8

Instruction: With the battery installed and referenced to its negative terminal, measure DC voltage on the positive line at the input and output of each control module and across each switch when it is in the ON position. Also probe across each red indicator LED/resistor pair. Confirm whether 12 V is present at the module inputs and whether it propagates through each switch to the next module. Note any module where the positive rail voltage drops or where an ON switch still shows a significant voltage difference across its contacts (indicating an internal open).
